Peter and his mother came to New_York especially for us , and both morning and afternoon sessions were recorded on the same day so that they could return to Atlantic City as soon as possible , especially since Jennifer's first birthday was August 10. Peter talked a great deal and was very active throughout the day. He is obviously having a wonderful time at the shore; he frequently played as if he were there , building imaginary sand castles , chasing dragon flies , etc. There has been considerable progess in toilet training although he had an "accident" during this session. He is growing taller and , without diapers , seems more boyish , less babyish. Peter enjoyed playing with crayons and paper , new at this session. He had a wonderful time when his father came home and drew with him for a few minutes. Peter imitated virtually every stroke of his father's crayon that he could and accompanied this with imitation of what his father said. Many of Peter's sentences are quite long and many are the same sentences used again and again in different , but appropriate situations. There are many "verb plus verb" sentences: gonna plus verb , wanta plus verb , can't plus verb , have_to plus verb. His negative sentences tend to be quite elaborate and were sometimes accompanied by the affirmative correlate. His imitation was rarely purely that: he usually changed the pronoun or added something more to his imitations. Nouns in subject position were extremely rare.
